# Copy to deploy/.env and fill in, then:
#   docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml up -d
#
# This is the ONLY place secrets/config for the self-hosted container live.
# deploy/.env is gitignored (matches the repo's own `.env` / `.env.*` /
# `!.env.example` pattern) — never commit your real values.

# Required for real encryption at rest. Portico encrypts session storage-state
# (cookies/local-storage that let a run skip login/2FA) with AES-256-GCM using
# this key (packages/store/src/crypto.ts). Leave unset and it still runs, but
# falls back to base64 ENCODING (not encryption) with a loud warning in the
# logs — fine for a first look, not for anything with real credentials.
# Must be >= 16 characters. Generate one with:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
PORTICO_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# --- Optional: self-heal / AI extraction tier ------------------------------
# Off the hot path of a promoted flow (a healthy run's latency is browser
# speed, not model speed) — used to recover a run when a step's target has
# drifted, and for AI-assisted extraction. See packages/engine/src/model.ts.
# PORTICO_HEAL_PROVIDER selects which key below is used; PORTICO_HEAL_API_KEY
# overrides both if set directly.
# PORTICO_HEAL_PROVIDER=anthropic   # "anthropic" | "openai"
# PORTICO_HEAL_MODEL=
# PORTICO_HEAL_API_KEY=

# --- Optional: agent authoring ("author by demonstration" in the console) -
# packages/author drives Stagehand, which reads OPENAI_API_KEY directly. Also
# used as the PORTICO_HEAL_API_KEY fallback when PORTICO_HEAL_PROVIDER=openai.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Fallback for PORTICO_HEAL_API_KEY when PORTICO_HEAL_PROVIDER=anthropic.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
